results.name: Smallest number beginning with 9 and having exactly n prime divisors counted with multiplicity.
program: (PARI) a(n) = {i = 2^n; while ((digits(i)[1] != 9) || (bigomega(i)!=n), i++); i;} \\ _Michel Marcus_, Sep 14 2013
